		   <br /><nobr><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Good [3.56]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Jiggidyjay&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>Just thought I'd add a few things to this...<br><br>It's called a <a href="HTTP://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=473" target="akztarg">Worker Sledgemallet</a>. As far as faction... if you're an agnostic bard and you have your DE mask, this shouldn't be a problem (unless you've killed a ton of mobs in KC). Go into DE illusion, drop faction song once if you want the extra insurance, and you're golden. If you're not an agnostic and have religion issues, you can always do the charm trick too. You can charm him to do the turnin. It's a lot quicker and easier then slaughtering hundreds of green mobs to raise faction. Also, IIRC, he only needs 1 jade.<br><br>When you use the proc to gate in, you don't have to worry about being summoned, as long as you're not dumb enough to try and fight a summoning mob. You have to do a certain percentage of damage (around 2-5%) before they'll start summoning you.<br><br>Make sure you don't fall into the hull of the ship. You used to be able to duck, crawl into a corner, stand and pop out. That doesn't work anymore. You have to be able to shadowstep or gate out now.<br><br>I applaud your post. It's always good to see someone trying to help.<br><br></p><br /><span class="sm">----------------------------</span><br /><a href="HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1006062" target="akztarg">Jiggidyjay</a> - <span class="sm">Mr Ranger</span class="sm"><br><a href="HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1003866" target="akztarg">Zingin Ansinging</a> - <span class="sm">Mr Bard of <a href="HTTP://firestorme